value.0: Lady Hedinfrid, the young and beautiful northern maiden of  lord Hallstein. She is said to be often the calming voice that has helped her husband to gain the unquestionable devotion of their kin.
This berserker seems to have lost in a discussion.

A young woman with honey colored hair, coppery skin and shining blue eyes. The low neckline of her dress and her confident movements place her in many day dreams, but the beauty of the maidens of the north is as great as their fury if one of the drunks forgets his place.

Edgar GÃ¦irvi is a huge man even by the standards of the berserkers, towering over seven feet of height. The ever vigilant gaze of his piercing blue eyes, his wisdom and his legendary skills in combat made him Lord Hallstein's closest advisor for years.

This berserker towers at a height of over six feet. His blonde hair, coppery tanned skin and light blue eyes mark him as one of the northmen that take refuge in the Skull Crags. The old armor that the man wears is made of furs and old decorated plate mail, in which a huge number of runes and totems carved in it.
This northmen is one of the Skalds, men or women that pass their kins history on through stories, ballads and song. A much needed task in the mostly illiterate society they live in.

Uthgar Gardolfsson, the son of Gardolf Beorunna, was a great and fierce warrior. His battle against Gurt, Lord of the Pale Giants, impressed even the god Tempus who then rewarded him by elevating him to godhood.

This large shield made out of wood and leather was created in memory and honor of this battle, offering additional protection against such gigantic foes of the local area.

This bearded greataxe is an master crafted specimen of its kind. The cutting edge of the bearded axe extends below the width of the throat, providing a wide cutting surface while keeping the overall weight of the axe low, made for giving a swift and powerful blow.

This bearded battleaxe is an master crafted specimen of its kind. The cutting edge of the bearded axe extends below the width of the throat, providing a wide cutting surface while keeping the overall weight of the axe low, made for giving a swift and clean blow.

Axes are the most commonly used weapons of the Uthgardt. They inflict a high amount of damage on impact with the ability to pull the enemy into the shield-line to strike them down while still being protected against the attack of others. Totemic runes inscribed into the handle of the axes have been said to take up a life of their own in battle, appearing as images of gigantic beasts, inspiring terror in the heart of foes.

Axes are the most commonly used weapons of the Uthgardt. These throwing axes are heavily weighted, but crafted so that they still maintain enough balance to be used as projectiles. Not only does this make them far stronger than a mundane axe, but can hit hard enough to inflict targets with a heavy concussion.
